  <prompt>
    Delete `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/CreateMatter/SendEmailStep.tsx` — the ONLY LegalWorkspace email-step fork (per CLAUDE.md DELTA #9 empirical finding). The fork's CreateMatter caller (within `LegalWorkspace/src/components/CreateMatter/`) must now consume the canonical `<SendEmailStep />` from `@spaarke/ui-components` (the same shared-lib path migrated in task 072 for the CreateMatterWizard surface).

    IMPORTANT empirical clarification: per CLAUDE.md DELTA #9, spec FR-25 phrasing "LegalWorkspace forks 5 wizards" overstates the per-file count. LegalWorkspace's CreateProject/CreateEvent/CreateTodo/CreateWorkAssignment directories EXIST but contain NO SendEmailStep file. There are no additional email-step forks in LegalWorkspace beyond the one CreateMatter file deleted here. Wave 5 scope is correspondingly smaller than FR-25 phrasing implied.

    Steps:
    1. Delete the fork file.
    2. Find any LegalWorkspace caller(s) that imported the deleted local SendEmailStep and switch them to import the canonical `<SendEmailStep />` from `@spaarke/ui-components`.
    3. Build LegalWorkspace solution to verify no orphan imports remain.

    NOTE per Owner Clarification: All Wave 5 changes ship as a single PR (task 076). Do not push as standalone.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke frontend engineer. Familiar with the LegalWorkspace solution structure and the shared `@spaarke/ui-components` public surface.
  </role>

  <goal>
