  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      LegalWorkspace historically forked email-step components from the shared library to avoid cross-package dependency. Spec FR-25 directs retirement of these forks. Per CLAUDE.md DELTA #9 (verified at pre-flight 2026-06-05), only the CreateMatter SendEmailStep is a genuine fork; the other 4 wizard dirs in LegalWorkspace exist but contain no SendEmailStep file. This makes Wave 5's LegalWorkspace cleanup a single-file delete rather than the 5-file delete the spec phrasing implied.

      Other LegalWorkspace email-touching forks (SummarizeFilesDialog, FilePreviewDialog) are handled by Waves 3 + 4 — outside this task's scope.
